<div>
<div bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
<div class="moz-cite-prefix">You have to pass HWLOC_MEMBIND_STRICT if you want an error code when the policy isn't supported.<br>
<br>
<br>
Assuming you get the nodeset of your current binding with get_area_membind_nodeset() in bindset, you can do something like this (untested):<br>
<br>
hwloc_bitmap_t bindset, totalset, newset;<br>
int i;<br>
/* get the total nodeset and duplicate it before modifying it */<br>
totalset = hwloc_bitmap_dup(hwloc_topology_get_topology_nodeset(topo));<br>
/* get the current binding */<br>
bindset = hwloc_bitmap_alloc();<br>
hwloc_get_area_membind_nodeset(topology, ..., bindset, ...);<br>
/* substract the nodeset where the buffer is already available */<br>
hwloc_bitmap_andnot(totalset, totalset, bindset);<br>
/* create a empty bitmap to play with inside the next loop */<br>
newset = hwloc_bitmap_alloc();<br>
/* iterate over remaining bits and alloc/bind there */<br>
hwloc_bitmap_foreach_begin(i, totalset) {<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp; hwloc_bitmap_only(newset, i);<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp; p = hwloc_alloc_membind_nodeset(...., newset, ...);<br>
}<br>
hwloc_bitmap_free(totalset);<br>
hwloc_bitmap_free(bindset);<br>
hwloc_bitmap_free(newset);<br>
<br>
Brice<br>
<br>
<br>
